00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,000
It's time to reveal...

23
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
And today, we're asking what happens

24
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,000
when we fall in love?

25
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Well, Dr Knowles, I happen to be

26
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,000
an expert in matters of the heart.

27
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Actually, Professor,

28
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
we don't love with our hearts, we love with our brains.

29
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
You wha...?

30
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
When we fall in love, a chemical called dopamine

31
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
floods the part of our brain that processes pleasure.

32
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,000
This gives us such a rush that it makes us literally crave

33
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
the other person.

34
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
However, we also experience a spike

35
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
in a hormone called adrenaline,

36
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
and this has some... Shall we say, noticeable physical effects.

37
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Your mouth dries out, your heart starts to race,

38
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
your palms get all sweaty...

39
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,000
'Tis fierce embarrassing, really.

40
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,000
It can be, Professor.

41
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
But before we go on, we need to take a short break.

42
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,000
And we are clear!

43
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
So, Colin. What have you got planned for later?

44
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Well, I think classic is the way to go, Doctor - flowers, chocolates,

45
