63
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:36,000
And if the person you love doesn't love you back, it can cause stress,

64
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:40,000
disturb your sleep and put you in a real bad mood.

65
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
So why do we bother with love at all?

66
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Well, love can go either way.

67
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Let's say the other person DOES like you

68
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
and you show each other affection.

69
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
The cuddle hormone, oxytocin,

70
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
is gradually released in your brain, giving you a warm,

71
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
fuzzy feeling that helps with trust and bonding.

72
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
It's enough to make you sick, isn't it?

73
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Anyway, I think it's time to wrap this one up.

74
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
So, as you've seen, we understand a little bit about what

75
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
happens in our brains when we fall in love.

76
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
But the old romantic in me knows that there's something

77
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
